{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GTepbYbnTDehnMhc3XqM2y","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on all my exploration, here's my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## BUG ANALYSIS REPORT: State Reconciliation Issue (Stories 16-5 through 16-8)\n\n### Location: State Reconciliation Code\n\n**Primary file:** `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/state.ts`\n\n**Function:** `reconcileState()` (lines 434-571)\n\n**Called from:** `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/run.ts` (line 112) - executes on every `codeharness run` session start\n\n### The Bug Mechanism\n\nThe reconciliation logic has a subtle but critical flaw in how it synchronizes sprint-state.json with sprint-status.yaml:\n\n**Line 495-518 in state.ts:**\n```typescript\n// 4. Import stories from sprint-status.yaml if stories is empty (unmigrated project)\nif (Object.keys(state.stories).length === 0) {\n  try {\n    const yamlStatuses = readSprintStatus(projectRoot());\n    // Imports ALL stories from YAML, overwriting state with default values\n    state.stories[key] = {\n      status: status as StoryStatus,\n      attempts: 0,  // RESET to 0!\n      lastAttempt: null,  // RESET to null!\n      lastError: null,\n      proofPath: null,  // LOST proof reference!\n      acResults: null,\n    };\n    changed = true;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nWhile this code only runs when `state.stories` is empty (condition line 496), there's a related issue:\n\n**When `writeStateAtomic()` is called (line 553), it regenerates sprint-status.yaml from the state:**\n\nLines 205-216 in state.ts:\n```typescript\nfunction writeSprintStatusYaml(state: SprintState): void {\n  try {\n    // ...regenerates YAML from current state...\n    writeFileSync(yamlPath, content, 'utf-8');\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### The Actual Reset Mechanism\n\nThe 12 repeated resets of stories 16-5 through 16-8 from `done` back to `review` is likely caused by:\n\n1. **Story completes** → sets status to `'review'` (line 43 in run.ts)\n2. **Session ends** → ralph exits\n3. **New session starts** → `reconcileState()` called (run.ts line 112)\n4. **If any reconciliation happens** → `writeStateAtomic()` regenerates YAML (state.ts line 553)\n5. **But the story state is already written with status='review'** from step 1\n6. **Next iteration** → YAML shows `review`, not `done`\n\n### Key Evidence\n\n1. **Import path found:** Line 498 in state.ts imports from `/src/lib/sync/index.js` → `readSprintStatus()`\n2. **Proof path loss:** Stories lose their `proofPath` values (line 507) when YAML is imported as the source of truth\n3. **Attempt counter reset:** Line 504 resets `attempts: 0` regardless of previous attempt history\n\n### Files Responsible\n\n| File | Location | Responsibility |\n|------|----------|-----------------|\n| `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` | Lines 434-571 | Reconciliation logic on session start |\n| `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` | Lines 205-216 | YAML regeneration (overwrites derived view) |\n| `src/commands/run.ts` | Line 112 | Calls reconcileState() on every session start |\n| `src/commands/run.ts` | Line 43 | Sets story status to 'review' on completion |\n| `src/lib/sync/sprint-yaml.ts` | Lines 11-32 | Reads YAML as secondary source |\n\n### The Root Cause\n\nThe design assumes sprint-state.json is the **source of truth** and sprint-status.yaml is a **derived view**, but the reconciliation logic (line 498-518) treats YAML as a fallback source when stories are empty—creating a bi-directional sync that can lose data."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2610e689-589b-4ec2-8784-d06d07275472","uuid":"9c8842b3-ec36-4482-97e3-ca7980f761d1","timestamp":"2026-03-27T14:56:03.456Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find the code responsible for \"state reconciliation\" in this codebase. The bug: stories 16-5 through 16-8 keep getting reset from `done` back to `review` in sprint-state.json every time ralph starts a new session. This has happened 12 times.\n\nSearch for:\n1. Any code that reads sprint-state.json and modifies story statuses\n2. Any \"reconciliation\" or \"sync\" logic that runs on session start\n3. Ralph's session initialization code that might be resetting state\n4. The code in `src/` that manages sprint-state.json writes\n\nFocus on files in: src/, ralph/\nLook for patterns like: reconcil, sync, session.*start, sprint.*state, status.*update, resetState","agentId":"ac751f21b418358c6","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on all my exploration, here's my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## BUG ANALYSIS REPORT: State Reconciliation Issue (Stories 16-5 through 16-8)\n\n### Location: State Reconciliation Code\n\n**Primary file:** `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/state.ts`\n\n**Function:** `reconcileState()` (lines 434-571)\n\n**Called from:** `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/run.ts` (line 112) - executes on every `codeharness run` session start\n\n### The Bug Mechanism\n\nThe reconciliation logic has a subtle but critical flaw in how it synchronizes sprint-state.json with sprint-status.yaml:\n\n**Line 495-518 in state.ts:**\n```typescript\n// 4. Import stories from sprint-status.yaml if stories is empty (unmigrated project)\nif (Object.keys(state.stories).length === 0) {\n  try {\n    const yamlStatuses = readSprintStatus(projectRoot());\n    // Imports ALL stories from YAML, overwriting state with default values\n    state.stories[key] = {\n      status: status as StoryStatus,\n      attempts: 0,  // RESET to 0!\n      lastAttempt: null,  // RESET to null!\n      lastError: null,\n      proofPath: null,  // LOST proof reference!\n      acResults: null,\n    };\n    changed = true;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nWhile this code only runs when `state.stories` is empty (condition line 496), there's a related issue:\n\n**When `writeStateAtomic()` is called (line 553), it regenerates sprint-status.yaml from the state:**\n\nLines 205-216 in state.ts:\n```typescript\nfunction writeSprintStatusYaml(state: SprintState): void {\n  try {\n    // ...regenerates YAML from current state...\n    writeFileSync(yamlPath, content, 'utf-8');\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### The Actual Reset Mechanism\n\nThe 12 repeated resets of stories 16-5 through 16-8 from `done` back to `review` is likely caused by:\n\n1. **Story completes** → sets status to `'review'` (line 43 in run.ts)\n2. **Session ends** → ralph exits\n3. **New session starts** → `reconcileState()` called (run.ts line 112)\n4. **If any reconciliation happens** → `writeStateAtomic()` regenerates YAML (state.ts line 553)\n5. **But the story state is already written with status='review'** from step 1\n6. **Next iteration** → YAML shows `review`, not `done`\n\n### Key Evidence\n\n1. **Import path found:** Line 498 in state.ts imports from `/src/lib/sync/index.js` → `readSprintStatus()`\n2. **Proof path loss:** Stories lose their `proofPath` values (line 507) when YAML is imported as the source of truth\n3. **Attempt counter reset:** Line 504 resets `attempts: 0` regardless of previous attempt history\n\n### Files Responsible\n\n| File | Location | Responsibility |\n|------|----------|-----------------|\n| `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` | Lines 434-571 | Reconciliation logic on session start |\n| `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` | Lines 205-216 | YAML regeneration (overwrites derived view) |\n| `src/commands/run.ts` | Line 112 | Calls reconcileState() on every session start |\n| `src/commands/run.ts` | Line 43 | Sets story status to 'review' on completion |\n| `src/lib/sync/sprint-yaml.ts` | Lines 11-32 | Reads YAML as secondary source |\n\n### The Root Cause\n\nThe design assumes sprint-state.json is the **source of truth** and sprint-status.yaml is a **derived view**, but the reconciliation logic (line 498-518) treats YAML as a fallback source when stories are empty—creating a bi-directional sync that can lose data."}],"totalDurationMs":85091,"totalTokens"