{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GKAggq7HU5eKvxQR3ercqD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue! The `parseRalphMessage` function parses `[SUCCESS] Story {key}: DONE` patterns from the output. When a claude session outputs this line (as part of the harness-run flow), the `run.ts` event handler intercepts it and calls `updateStoryStatus(key, 'review')` — which sets the story BACK to `review`!\n\nThis is the smoking gun:\n1. A claude session processes a story and prints `[OK] Story 16-5-xxx: verifying → done`\n2. The output goes through ralph's stdout to `codeharness run`'s line handler\n\n\n3. The line handler's `parseRalphMessage` matches `[SUCCESS] Story 16-5-xxx: DONE`\n4. `handleAgentEvent` fires with `story-complete` event\n5. `updateStoryStatus('16-5-xxx', 'review')` sets the story to `review` in sprint-state.json\n\nNow I need to verify whether the `[OK]` lines actually match the `SUCCESS_STORY` regex pattern.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":749,"cache_read_input_tokens":81174,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":749},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2610e689-589b-4ec2-8784-d06d07275472","uuid":"c6865432-b8e3-4ba2-8c92-9f31fbfca134"}
