{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UvbhfP2x1vAcdLWEJkAV8G","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2610e689-589b-4ec2-8784-d06d07275472","uuid":"8198be6b-8ba4-4e88-8ffe-b82b39ca319e","timestamp":"2026-03-27T15:05:06.252Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 20 — state corruption fix #11, no-op (2026-03-27T18:50Z)","newString":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 21 — ROOT CAUSE FOUND for state corruption (2026-03-27T19:15Z)\n\n- **ROOT CAUSE IDENTIFIED**: `parseRalphMessage()` in `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` matches `[SUCCESS] Story {key}: DONE` regex within stream-json NDJSON lines. When claude session output contains tool results or text that includes these patterns (e.g., reading test files, source code, or discussing story completions), the regex matches inside the JSON envelope.\n- `handleAgentEvent()` in `run.ts:41-48` then calls `updateStoryStatus(key, 'review')`, which CREATES new story entries (line 347: `?? defaultStoryState()`) or resets existing `done` stories to `review`.\n- **Evidence**: This session created 3 phantom stories: `16-5-xxx`, `16-5-foo`, `1-1-foo` — all from patterns in session output. The `1-1-foo` came directly from test file `ralph.test.ts` line: `driver.parseOutput('[SUCCESS] Story 1-1-foo: DONE')`.\n- **Fix needed**: `parseRalphMessage()` must NOT match within JSON lines. Add a check: if the line starts with `{`, skip ralph pattern matching entirely (it's a stream-json line, let the stream-json parser handle it).\n- **Secondary fix**: `updateStoryStatus()` should NOT create new story entries. Change `?? defaultStoryState()` to return an error if the story key doesn't exist.\n- Fixed: removed 3 phantom stories, restored sprint counts to 74/74.\n- All 74 real stories remain done.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~25\n- By tool: Read: 8, Grep: 6, Bash: 5, Edit: 6, Agent: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: git diff (~80 lines), python3 state fix (~1 line)\n- Files read: ~10 unique, ~15 total reads (sprint-state.json read 4+ times, state.ts read 3 times)\n- Redundant operations: Multiple reads of sprint-state.json as file kept being externally modified\n\n### Session 20 — state corruption fix #11, no-op (2026-03-27T18:50Z)","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 20 — state corruption fix #11, no-op (2026-03-27T18:50Z)\n\n- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and 10 previous sessions fixing this.\n- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.\n- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70, should be 74.\n- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74 in both files.\n- Root cause: ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting story statuses. 11th occurrence today. This is a critical bug that has wasted ~$20+ in API calls across 11 sessions.\n- No actual story work was done — all 74 stories are done.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1\n- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Entire session is redundant — same state corruption fix applied for the 11th time\n\n### Session 19 — state corruption fix #10, no-op (2026-03-27T15:16Z)\n\n- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and 9 previous sessions fixing this.\n- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.\n- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70, should be 74.\n- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74 in both files.\n- Root cause: ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting story statuses. 10th occurrence today. This is a critical bug.\n- No actual story work was done — all 74 stories are done.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Read: 6, Edit: 3, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Bash: 1\n- Files read: 4 unique, 7 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Entire session is redundant — same state corruption fix applied for the 10th time\n\n### Session 18 — retrospective only (2026-03-27T14:50Z)\n\n- NO-OP session. All 74 stories already done.\n- Ran `codeharness stats --save` to refresh cost report.\n- Wrote session 17 retrospective to session-retro-2026-03-27.md.\n- No state edits needed — state was already corrected in session 17.\n- Total project cost: $639.78 across 4,742 API calls.\n- Estimated waste from 9 state-corruption sessions: $13-18.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~8\n- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 1, Bash: 2\n- Files read: 4 unique\n- Redundant operations: None — this session only produced the retro\n\n### Session 17 — state corruption fix #9 (2026-03-27T14:42Z)\n\n- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and 8 previous sessions fixing this.\n- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.\n- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70, should be 74.\n- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74 in both files.\n- Root cause: ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting story statuses. 9th occurrence today. This is a bug in the reconciliation logic that needs to be fixed as a priority.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Read: 5, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1\n- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Entire session is redundant — same state corruption fix applied for the 9th time\n\n### Session 16 — state corruption fix #8 (2026-03-27T14:38Z)\n\n- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and previous 7 sessions fixing this.\n- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.\n- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70, should be 74.\n- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74 in both files.\n- Root cause persists: ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting story statuses. This is the 8th occurrence today.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 5, Grep: 3, Glob: 1\n- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Entire session is redundant — same state corruption fix applied for the 8th time\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":5,"newStart":1,"newLines":22,"lines":[" # Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27"," ","+### Session 21 — ROOT CAUSE FOUND for state corruption (2026-03-27T19:15Z)","+","+- **ROOT CAUSE IDENTIFIED**: `parseRalphMessage()` in `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` matches `[SUCCESS] Story {key}: DONE` regex within stream-json NDJSON lines. When claude session output contains tool results or text that includes these patterns (e.g., reading test files, source code, or discussing story completions), the regex matches inside the JSON envelope.","+- `handleAgentEvent()` in `run.ts:41-48` then calls `updateStoryStatus(key, 'review')`, which CREATES new story entries (line 347: `?? defaultStoryState()`) or resets existing `done` stories to `review`.","+- **Evidence**: This session created 3 phantom stories: `16-5-xxx`, `16-5-foo`, `1-1-foo` — all from patterns in session output. The `1-1-foo` came directly from test file `ralph.test.ts` line: `driver.parseOutput('[SUCCESS] Story 1-1-foo: DONE')`.","+- **Fix needed**: `parseRalphMessage()` must NOT match within JSON lines. Add a check: if the line starts with `{`, skip ralph pattern matching entirely (it's a stream-json line, let the stream-json parser handle it).","+- **Secondary fix**: `updateStoryStatus()` should NOT create new story entries. Change `?? defaultStoryState()` to return an error if the story key doesn't exist.","+- Fixed: removed 3 phantom stories, restored sprint counts to 74/74.","+- All 74 real stories remain done.","+","+## Token Report","+- Total tool calls: ~25","+- By tool: Read: 8, Grep: 6, Bash: 5, Edit: 6, Agent: 1","+- Largest Bash outputs: git diff (~80 lines), python3 state fix (~1 line)","+- Files read: ~10 unique, ~15 total reads (sprint-state.json read 4+ times, state.ts read 3 times)","+- Redundant operations: Multiple reads of sprint-state.json as file kept being externally modified","+"," ### Session 20 — state corruption fix #11, no-op (2026-03-27T18:50Z)"," "," - Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and 10 previous sessions fixing this."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
