{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012Ps2m2hMCo8MbrVSoqmraq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[OK] Session retrospective complete\n\n---\n\n## Session 21 Summary\n\n**No story work** — all 74 stories are done.\n\n**Root cause of state corruption found.** The bug that wasted 12+ sessions (~$22-30 in API costs):\n\n1. `parseRalphMessage()` in `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts:53` uses regex `[SUCCESS] Story {key}: DONE` without checking if the line is a stream-json NDJSON object\n2. When claude session output contains these patterns inside JSON envelopes (tool results reading test files, source code, etc.), the regex matches within the JSON string\n3. `run.ts:43` calls `updateStoryStatus(key, 'review')`, which resets `done` stories to `review` or creates phantom entries (via `?? defaultStoryState()` on line 347 of `state.ts`)\n\n**Evidence from this session:** 3 phantom stories created live: `16-5-xxx`, `16-5-foo`, `1-1-foo`\n\n**Two fixes needed:**\n1. **`ralph.ts` `parseOutput()`** — if the line starts with `{`, skip `parseRalphMessage()` entirely and go straight to the stream-json parser\n2. **`state.ts` `updateStoryStatus()`** — return an error if the story key doesn't exist instead of creating it with `defaultStoryState()`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1227,"cache_read_input_tokens":94257,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1227},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2610e689-589b-4ec2-8784-d06d07275472","uuid":"e7eea613-668e-4a48-86ba-c6a7ffb0acbe"}
